typeProperties.script:
source(output(
		CALL_SUMMARY_ID as string,
		PARENT_CALL_AID as string,
		LOCAL_CALL_DATE_ID as string,
		CALL_DATE_ID as string,
		TERRITORY_ID as string,
		CYCLE as string,
		SALES_FORCE_KEY as string,
		DATE as string,
		LOCAL_CALL_TIME_ID as string,
		ACCOUNT_ID as string,
		CALL_NAME as string,
		RX_CALL_TYPE as string,
		CALL_STATUS as string,
		ATTENDEE_TYPE as string,
		CLM_IND as string,
		SAMPLE_CALL_IND as string,
		CALL_TYPE as string,
		DETAILED_PRODUCTS as string,
		DURATION as string,
		CREATED_DATE_ID as string,
		CREATED_DATE_TIME_ID as string,
		LAST_MODIFIED_DATE_ID as string,
		LAST_MODIFIED_DATE_TIME_ID as string,
		PRE_CALL_NOTES as string,
		NEXT_CALL_NOTES as string,
		REVIEW_STATUS as string,
		ACCOUNT_NAME as string,
		RX_LEGAL_ID as string,
		KEY_MESSAGE_NAME as string,
		QUESTION_ID as string,
		PRODUCT as string,
		CALL_DATE as string,
		ORIGEM as string
	),
	allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	ignoreNoFilesFound: false,
	format: 'parquet',
	wildcardPaths:['synapse/workspaces/gsk-synapse/warehouse/dash.gso/fato_gso_call_summary.parquet'],
	partitionBy('hash', 1)) ~> fGsoCallSummarySource
source(output(
		SURVEY_KEY as string,
		QUESTION_ID as string,
		SOURCE_CREATED_TS as string,
		RESPONSE_LAST_MODIFIED_TS as string,
		SOURCE_USER_AID as string,
		QUESTION_RESPONSE_ID as string,
		RESPONSE_NAME as string,
		RESPONSE_NUMBER as string,
		RESPONSE as string,
		PRODUCT as string,
		RESPONSE_QUESTION_ORDER as string,
		DATE as string,
		TARGET_LAST_MODIFIED_TS as string,
		MODIFIED_DATE as string,
		START_DATE_ID as string,
		END_DATE_ID as string,
		REVIEW_DATE_ID as string,
		REVIEW_STATUS as string,
		MANAGER_TERRITORY_ID as string,
		EMPLOYEE_TERRITORY_ID as string,
		TERRITORY_ID as string,
		DATE_DIFF as string,
		FLAG_PREMIO as string,
		SALES_FORCE_KEY as string,
		RESPONSES_KEY as string,
		ORIGEM as string
	),
	allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	ignoreNoFilesFound: false,
	format: 'parquet',
	wildcardPaths:['synapse/workspaces/gsk-synapse/warehouse/dash.gso/fato_gso_response.parquet'],
	partitionBy('hash', 1)) ~> fGsoResponseSource
source(output(
		RX_EXTERNAL_ID as string,
		USER_ID as string,
		SF_SOURCE_USER_AID as string,
		USER_NAME as string,
		FIRST_NAME as string,
		NAME as string,
		LAST_NAME as string,
		COUNTRY as string,
		STATE_PROVINCE as string,
		CITY as string,
		POSTAL_CODE as string,
		ACTIVE_IND as string,
		EMAIL as string,
		EMPLOYEE_NUMBER_AID as string,
		USER_IDENTIFIER_AID as string,
		CORE_GSK_FUNCTIONAL_PROFILE as string,
		PROFILE_NAME as string
	),
	allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	ignoreNoFilesFound: false,
	format: 'parquet',
	wildcardPaths:['synapse/workspaces/gsk-synapse/warehouse/dash.gso/dim_sales_force_teradata.parquet'],
	partitionBy('hash', 1)) ~> dSalesForceTeradata
source(output(
		RX_EXTERNAL_ID as string,
		UF as string
	),
	allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	ignoreNoFilesFound: false,
	format: 'parquet',
	wildcardPaths:['synapse/workspaces/gsk-synapse/warehouse/dash.gso/dim_sales_force_funcionario.parquet'],
	partitionBy('hash', 1)) ~> dSalesForceFuncionario
source(output(
		RX_EXTERNAL_ID as string,
		CICLO as string,
		SALES_FORCE_KEY as string,
		SF_KEY as string,
		ROW_ID_TERRITORIO as string,
		ROW_ID_GD as string,
		NOME_GD as string,
		NOME_GR as string,
		TERRITORIO_GD as string,
		TERRITORIO_GR as string,
		BU as string,
		{DIVISÃO} as string,
		TERRITORIO as string,
		NOME_REP as string
	),
	allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	ignoreNoFilesFound: false,
	format: 'parquet',
	wildcardPaths:['synapse/workspaces/gsk-synapse/warehouse/dash.gso/dim_sales_force_sqlserver.parquet'],
	partitionBy('hash', 1)) ~> dSalesForceSqlServer
source(output(
		AREA as string,
		UF as string,
		REGION as string,
		STATE as string
	),
	allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	ignoreNoFilesFound: false,
	format: 'parquet',
	wildcardPaths:['synapse/workspaces/gsk-synapse/warehouse/dash.gso/dim_region.parquet'],
	partitionBy('hash', 1)) ~> dSalesForceRegiao
source(output(
		QUESTION_ID as string,
		QUESTION_CREATED_DATE as string,
		QUESTION_NAME as string,
		QUESTION_LAST_MODIFIED_TS as string,
		QUESTION_TEXT as string,
		QUESTION_ORDER as string,
		QUESTION_TYPE as string,
		TIPO_QUESTAO as string
	),
	allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	ignoreNoFilesFound: false,
	format: 'parquet',
	wildcardPaths:['synapse/workspaces/gsk-synapse/warehouse/dash.gso/dim_survey_question.parquet']) ~> dSurveyQuestion
source(output(
		SURVEY_KEY as string,
		VISIT_DATE as string,
		VISIT_PRODUCT as string,
		TOTAL_VISITS as string
	),
	allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	ignoreNoFilesFound: false,
	format: 'parquet',
	wildcardPaths:['synapse/workspaces/gsk-synapse/warehouse/dash.gso/dim_visits.parquet']) ~> dVisits
source(output(
		Region as string,
		Cluster as string,
		Country as string,
		SLSL as string,
		FLSL as string,
		City as string,
		{Business Unit} as string,
		{Field Visit/ Coaching Date} as date,
		Brand as string,
		{Total Number of Calls Observed} as short,
		{Number of GSO} as short,
		{1. FLSL builds a motivational and inspirational environment in the opening and during the coaching session } as short,
		{2. FLSL and Sales Rep agree to the coaching objective/goal } as short,
		{3. Coaching objective/goal is sequential (Checking previous action) } as short,
		{4. FLSL and Sales Rep mention and discuss the current performance } as short,
		{5. Clarity about the potential impact of the current performance is discussed } as short,
		{6. FLSL and Sales Rep Identify block/barriers to the current performance } as short,
		{7. Sales Rep gives some solutions to unblock the barriers } as short,
		{8. FLSL evaluates with Sales Rep the solutions to unblock barriers vs impact } as short,
		{9. FLSL offers alternative solutions } as short,
		{10. Explores with Sales Rep the - what, how and when it will be the next steps } as short,
		{11. Manager asks Sales Rep what further support he/she needs (discuss  the resources) } as short,
		{12. Builds the action plan and defines the success measures } as short,
		{13. Identifies the most important action/task to improve capability and maps the top skill / will gaps } as short,
		{14. Determines the best coaching style (Confront / Direct / Guide / Facilitate / Delegate) and  flexes the coaching style when necessary } as short,
		{Insightful Questions, Active Listening& Feedback SBI (Situation, Behavior & Impact):} as string,
		{Action Plans:} as string
	),
	allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	ignoreNoFilesFound: false,
	format: 'excel',
	container: 'gsksynapsestorage',
	sheetName: 'GCO',
	firstRowAsHeader: true,
	wildcardPaths:['synapse/workspaces/gsk-synapse/warehouse/aux.tabelas_auxiliares/GCO Pharma Summary*']) ~> dGCO
fGsoResponseSource, fGsoCallSummarySource union(byName: true,
	partitionBy('hash', 1))~> UniaoFato
dSalesForceTeradata, dSalesForceFuncionario join(dSalesForceTeradata@RX_EXTERNAL_ID == dSalesForceFuncionario@RX_EXTERNAL_ID,
	joinType:'left',
	partitionBy('hash', 1),
	broadcast: 'auto')~> LeftJoinFuncionario
LeftJoinFuncionario select(mapColumn(
		RX_EXTERNAL_ID = dSalesForceTeradata@RX_EXTERNAL_ID,
		USER_ID,
		SF_SOURCE_USER_AID,
		USER_NAME,
		FIRST_NAME,
		NAME,
		LAST_NAME,
		COUNTRY,
		STATE_PROVINCE,
		CITY,
		POSTAL_CODE,
		ACTIVE_IND,
		EMAIL,
		EMPLOYEE_NUMBER_AID,
		USER_IDENTIFIER_AID,
		CORE_GSK_FUNCTIONAL_PROFILE,
		PROFILE_NAME,
		RX_EXTERNAL_ID = dSalesForceFuncionario@RX_EXTERNAL_ID,
		UF
	),
	partitionBy('hash', 1),
	skipDuplicateMapInputs: true,
	skipDuplicateMapOutputs: true) ~> SelecionarValoresUnicos
SelecionarValoresUnicos, dSalesForceSqlServer join(SelecionarValoresUnicos@RX_EXTERNAL_ID == dSalesForceSqlServer@RX_EXTERNAL_ID,
	joinType:'left',
	partitionBy('hash', 1),
	broadcast: 'auto')~> LeftJoinSalesForceSQLSERVER
LeftJoinSalesForceSQLSERVER select(mapColumn(
		RX_EXTERNAL_ID = SelecionarValoresUnicos@RX_EXTERNAL_ID,
		USER_ID,
		SF_SOURCE_USER_AID,
		USER_NAME,
		FIRST_NAME,
		NAME,
		LAST_NAME,
		COUNTRY,
		STATE_PROVINCE,
		CITY,
		POSTAL_CODE,
		ACTIVE_IND,
		EMAIL,
		EMPLOYEE_NUMBER_AID,
		USER_IDENTIFIER_AID,
		CORE_GSK_FUNCTIONAL_PROFILE,
		PROFILE_NAME,
		UF,
		RX_EXTERNAL_ID = dSalesForceSqlServer@RX_EXTERNAL_ID,
		CICLO,
		SALES_FORCE_KEY,
		SF_KEY,
		ROW_ID_TERRITORIO,
		ROW_ID_GD,
		NOME_GD,
		NOME_GR,
		TERRITORIO_GD,
		TERRITORIO_GR,
		BU,
		DIVISAO = {DIVISÃO},
		TERRITORIO,
		NOME_REP
	),
	partitionBy('hash', 1),
	skipDuplicateMapInputs: true,
	skipDuplicateMapOutputs: true) ~> SelecionarValoresUnicos2
SelecionarValoresUnicos2, dSalesForceRegiao join(SelecionarValoresUnicos2@UF == dSalesForceRegiao@UF,
	joinType:'left',
	partitionBy('hash', 1),
	broadcast: 'auto')~> LeftJoinRegiao
LeftJoinRegiao select(mapColumn(
		RX_EXTERNAL_ID,
		USER_ID,
		SF_SOURCE_USER_AID,
		USER_NAME,
		FIRST_NAME,
		NAME,
		LAST_NAME,
		COUNTRY,
		STATE_PROVINCE,
		CITY,
		POSTAL_CODE,
		ACTIVE_IND,
		EMAIL,
		EMPLOYEE_NUMBER_AID,
		USER_IDENTIFIER_AID,
		CORE_GSK_FUNCTIONAL_PROFILE,
		PROFILE_NAME,
		UF = SelecionarValoresUnicos2@UF,
		CICLO,
		SALES_FORCE_KEY,
		SF_KEY,
		ROW_ID_TERRITORIO,
		ROW_ID_GD,
		NOME_GD,
		NOME_GR,
		TERRITORIO_GD,
		TERRITORIO_GR,
		BU,
		DIVISAO,
		TERRITORIO,
		NOME_REP,
		AREA,
		UF = SelecionarValoresUnicos2@UF,
		REGION,
		STATE
	),
	partitionBy('hash', 1),
	skipDuplicateMapInputs: true,
	skipDuplicateMapOutputs: true) ~> SelecaoFinal
dGCO select(mapColumn(
		REGION = Region,
		CLUSTER = Cluster,
		COUNTRY = Country,
		SLSL,
		FLSL,
		CITY = City,
		BUSINESS_UNIT = {Business Unit},
		FIELD_VISIT_COACHING_DATE = {Field Visit/ Coaching Date},
		BRAND = Brand,
		TOTAL_NUMBER_CALLS_OBSERVED = {Total Number of Calls Observed},
		NUMBER_OF_GSO = {Number of GSO},
		FLSL_MOTIVATIONAL_INSPIRATIONAL_ENVIRONMENT = {1. FLSL builds a motivational and inspirational environment in the opening and during the coaching session },
		FLSL_SALES_REP_AGREE_GOAL = {2. FLSL and Sales Rep agree to the coaching objective/goal },
		COACHING_GOAL_SEQUENTIAL_PREVIOUS_ACTION = {3. Coaching objective/goal is sequential (Checking previous action) },
		FLSL_SALES_REP_MENTION_CURRENT_PERFORMANCE = {4. FLSL and Sales Rep mention and discuss the current performance },
		POTENTIAL_IMPACT_CURRENT_PERFORMANCE = {5. Clarity about the potential impact of the current performance is discussed },
		FLSL_SALES_REP_BLOCK_CURRENT_PERFORMANCE = {6. FLSL and Sales Rep Identify block/barriers to the current performance },
		SALES_REP_SOLUTIONS_UNBLOCK_BARRIERS = {7. Sales Rep gives some solutions to unblock the barriers },
		FLSL_SALES_REP_SOLUTIONS_UNBLOCK_BARRIERS_IMPACT = {8. FLSL evaluates with Sales Rep the solutions to unblock barriers vs impact },
		FLSL_OFFERS_ALTERNATIVE_SOLUTIONS = {9. FLSL offers alternative solutions },
		EXPLORE_SALES_REP_NEXT_STEPS = {10. Explores with Sales Rep the - what, how and when it will be the next steps },
		MANAGER_ASKS_SALES_REP_SUPPORT_NEEDS = {11. Manager asks Sales Rep what further support he/she needs (discuss  the resources) },
		BUILDS_PLAN_SUCCESS_MEASURES = {12. Builds the action plan and defines the success measures },
		IMPORTANT_ACTION_IMPROVE_CAPABILITY_MAPS_TOP_SKILL = {13. Identifies the most important action/task to improve capability and maps the top skill / will gaps },
		DETERMINES_COACHING_STYLE_FLEXES_COACHING_STYLE = {14. Determines the best coaching style (Confront / Direct / Guide / Facilitate / Delegate) and  flexes the coaching style when necessary },
		QUESTIONS_ACTIVE_LISTENING_FEEDBACK_SBI = {Insightful Questions, Active Listening& Feedback SBI (Situation, Behavior & Impact):},
		ACTION_PLANS = {Action Plans:}
	),
	skipDuplicateMapInputs: true,
	skipDuplicateMapOutputs: true) ~> SelecaoGCO
SelecaoGCO derive(NUMBER_OF_GSO = coalesce(NUMBER_OF_GSO,0)) ~> CoalesceColumnNGSO
UniaoFato sink(allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	format: 'parquet',
	partitionFileNames:['fato_gso.parquet'],
	partitionBy('hash', 1),
	skipDuplicateMapInputs: true,
	skipDuplicateMapOutputs: true,
	saveOrder: 1) ~> FatoGsoDestino
SelecaoFinal sink(allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	format: 'parquet',
	partitionFileNames:['dimensao_sales_force.parquet'],
	mapColumn(
		RX_EXTERNAL_ID,
		USER_ID,
		SF_SOURCE_USER_AID,
		USER_NAME,
		FIRST_NAME,
		NAME,
		LAST_NAME,
		COUNTRY,
		STATE_PROVINCE,
		CITY,
		POSTAL_CODE,
		ACTIVE_IND,
		EMAIL,
		EMPLOYEE_NUMBER_AID,
		USER_IDENTIFIER_AID,
		CORE_GSK_FUNCTIONAL_PROFILE,
		PROFILE_NAME,
		UF,
		CICLO,
		SALES_FORCE_KEY,
		SF_KEY,
		ROW_ID_TERRITORIO,
		ROW_ID_GD,
		NOME_GD,
		NOME_GR,
		TERRITORIO_GD,
		TERRITORIO_GR,
		BU,
		DIVISAO,
		TERRITORIO,
		NOME_REP,
		AREA,
		REGION,
		STATE
	),
	partitionBy('hash', 1),
	skipDuplicateMapInputs: true,
	skipDuplicateMapOutputs: true,
	saveOrder: 2) ~> SalesForceDestino
dSurveyQuestion sink(allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	format: 'parquet',
	partitionFileNames:['dimensao_survey_question.parquet'],
	partitionBy('hash', 1),
	skipDuplicateMapInputs: true,
	skipDuplicateMapOutputs: true,
	saveOrder: 2) ~> SinkDimSurveyQuestion
dVisits sink(allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	format: 'parquet',
	partitionFileNames:['dimensao_visits.parquet'],
	partitionBy('hash', 1),
	skipDuplicateMapInputs: true,
	skipDuplicateMapOutputs: true,
	saveOrder: 2) ~> SinkDimVisits
CoalesceColumnNGSO sink(allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	format: 'parquet',
	partitionFileNames:['dimensao_gco.parquet'],
	partitionBy('hash', 1),
	skipDuplicateMapInputs: true,
	skipDuplicateMapOutputs: true) ~> SinkGCO
